.TH "__device_add_disk" 9 "__device_add_disk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__device_add_disk \- add disk information to kernel list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __device_add_disk
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "struct gendisk *disk "  ","
.BI "const struct attribute_group **groups "  ","
.BI "bool register_queue "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
parent device for the disk
.IP "disk" 12
per-device partitioning information
.IP "groups" 12
Additional per-device sysfs groups
.IP "register_queue" 12
register the queue if set to true
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function registers the partitioning information in \fIdisk\fP
with the kernel.

